  params_section: |md
    ### Parameter Indices (trait_param enum)
    ```cpp
    [0] HEBBIAN_RATE       // pre * post correlation
    [1] PRESYNAPTIC_RATE   // presynaptic activity
    [2] POSTSYNAPTIC_RATE  // postsynaptic activity
    [3] MAX_WEIGHT         // maximum weight bound
    [4] MIN_WEIGHT         // minimum weight bound
    [5] LEARNING_SIGNAL    // modulation signal
    [6] RESERVED_1
    [7] RESERVED_2
    ```
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#B87333"
      stroke: "#CD7F32"
      stroke-width: 2
      font-color: "#2D2D2D"
    }
  }

  methods_section: |md
    ### Methods
    ```cpp
    static trait average(t1, t2)
    void mutate(power, prob)
    bool is_learning_enabled()
    // true if trait_id in [2,4]
    exfloat hebbian_rate()
    exfloat presynaptic_rate()
    exfloat postsynaptic_rate()
    exfloat max_weight()
    exfloat min_weight()
    ```
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#4A5568"
      stroke: "#708090"
      stroke-width: 2
      font-color: "#E8DCC8"
    }
  }
}

# ============================================================================
# ACTIVATION FUNCTIONS
# ============================================================================
activation_funcs: |md
  ## ai_func_type enum
  **include/functions.hpp**
  ---
  ```cpp
  RELU      = 0  // max(0, x)
  LINEAR    = 1  // x
  HEAVISIDE = 2  // x >= 0 ? 1 : 0
  LOGISTIC  = 3  // 1 / (1 + e^-x)
  SIGMOID   = 4  // 2 / (1 + e^-x) - 1
  TANH      = 5  // tanh(x)
  GELU      = 6  // gaussian error linear
  SWISH     = 7  // x * sigmoid(x)
  LEAKY_RELU = 8 // x > 0 ? x : 0.01x
  NORMALIZE = 9  // x / alpha
  ```
| {
  style: {
    fill: "#3A3A3A"
    stroke: "#8A9A5B"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#D2B48C"
    border-radius: 4
  }
}

